body:
Hi, Iwant to erode my black and white image using a disc. My code is currently:

            using var paint = new SKPaint
            {
                ColorFilter = SKColorFilter.CreateTable(table), // Converts gray to true black/white
                ImageFilter = SKImageFilter.CreateErode(dilationRadius, dilationRadius),
            };

            var result = new SKBitmap(img.Info.Width, img.Info.Height, SKColorType.Bgra8888, SKAlphaType.Opaque);
            using var canvas = new SKCanvas(result);
            canvas.DrawBitmap(img, 0, 0, paint);
            return result;

But the resulting image looks like it was eroded with a square. I have not found any way so far to provide a custom geometry to the CreateErode function. Is there a way to do this?

I have used MATLAB in the past and that has multiple functions to create a "structuring element" first and then derives the erosion from that. So one can choose a line, a square or a circle. (Or provide a custom shape). But CreateErode only accepts 2 params for what I guess are the 2 dimensions of a rect.

The image still has sharp corners:

<img src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5293502/220184021-9a28c850-32db-40be-aa9a-b9a76c3298c3.png" width=300px>
